{
  "id": "ALAS2023-2026-1488",
  "title": "Amazon Linux 2023 - ALAS2023-2026-1488: Important priority package update for kernel6.12",
  "issued": {
    "date": "2026-03-16 09:00:00"
  },
  "updated": {
    "date": "2026-03-27 15:31:00"
  },
  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2023 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2026-23140:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpf, test_run: Subtract size of xdp_frame from allowed metadata size\n\nCVE-2026-23136:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nlibceph: reset sparse-read state in osd_fault()\n\nCVE-2026-23047:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nlibceph: make calc_target() set t-\u003epaused, not just clear it\n\nCVE-2026-22994:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpf: Fix reference count leak in bpf_prog_test_run_xdp()\n\nCVE-2026-22992:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nlibceph: return the handler error from mon_handle_auth_done()\n\nCVE-2026-22991:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nlibceph: make free_choose_arg_map() resilient to partial allocation\n\nCVE-2026-22990:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nlibceph: replace overzealous BUG_ON in osdmap_apply_incremental()\n\nCVE-2026-22989:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnfsd: check that server is running in unlock_filesystem\n\nCVE-2026-22984:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nlibceph: prevent potential out-of-bounds reads in handle_auth_done()\n\nCVE-2026-22980:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnfsd: provide locking for v4_end_grace\n\nCVE-2026-22979:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: fix memory leak in skb_segment_list for GRO packets\n\nCVE-2026-22978:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nwifi: avoid kernel-infoleak from struct iw_point\n\nCVE-2026-22977:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: sock: fix hardened usercopy panic in sock_recv_errqueue\n\nCVE-2026-22976:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet/sched: sch_qfq: Fix NULL deref when deactivating inactive aggregate in qfq_reset\n\nCVE-2025-71184:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbtrfs: fix NULL dereference on root when tracing inode eviction\n\nCVE-2025-71183:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbtrfs: always detect conflicting inodes when logging inode refs\n\nCVE-2025-71182:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncan: j1939: make j1939_session_activate() fail if device is no longer registered\n\nCVE-2025-71160:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnetfilter: nf_tables: avoid chain re-validation if possible\n\nCVE-2025-71144:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmptcp: ensure context reset on disconnect()\n\nCVE-2025-71134:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmm/page_alloc: change all pageblocks migrate type on coalescing\n\nCVE-2025-71088:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmptcp: fallback earlier on simult connection\n\nCVE-2025-68792:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ntpm2-sessions: Fix out of range indexing in name_size\n\nCVE-2025-40149:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ntls: Use __sk_dst_get() and dst_dev_rcu() in get_netdev_for_sock().\n",
